(2710, 1, '2018-03-12 07:38:39', '2018-03-12 07:38:39', '<p>Skyn The Day Spa, featuring a complete range of services, including custom facials, massage therapy, body treatments, laser hair removal, and hair and nail services for women and men.</p><p>Skyn The Day&nbsp; Spa has expanded on this meaning by creating a very special getaway that will leave you looking and feeling your absolute best!</p><p>Skyn The Day Spa opened in 2002, providing custom facials, massage therapy, and nail services. Owner Mandy Rohde saw a need for a true spa experience, with a peaceful ambiance and incredibly high level of service.  Amenity recently expanded its services with the addition of its state of the art full service Soho Hair Studio, with a team of master precision cutters and colorists.  Since our state-of-the-art facility and professional staff are uniquely dedicated to spa, hair, nail, and makeup services, your visit will be exclusive and personalized.</p><p>To meet all your perfectly polished needs, we’ve recently renovated our nail salon with all new pedicure chairs and manicure stations, as well as a 6 person drying station for you and your friends to relax in luxury.</p><p>We want your visit to be exclusive and personalized and we pride ourselves in putting together a staff of true professionals mastered in their crafts.  At Amenity Day Spa, you will retreat into a luxurious world of relaxation and rejuvenation like no other! Please sit back, relax, and enjoy the escape.</p>', 'Skyn The Day Spa', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'skyn-the-day-spa', '', '', '2018-03-12 07:38:39', '2018-03-12 07:38:39', '', 0, 'https://listing.downtown-directory.com/beauty-salon/backup/?post_type=listing&amp;p=2710', 0, 'listing', '', 2),
(2717, 1, '2018-03-12 08:06:13', '2018-03-12 08:06:13', 'Kevin\'s Barber Shop is located in Bronx, NY, USA “Shepherd Market”, in a wonderfully charming small square hidden between Piccadilly and Curzon Street in the exclusive batber shop itself is named after the infamous 15 days fair that took place on the site that is now known as Shepherd Market. It was developed in 1735-46 by Edward Shepherd. It comprises of a number of small side streets with a variety of boutique shops, restaurants and impressive pubs.<p>This is where Ivor Edwards decided would be the ideal place for his barber shop. The Barber Shop Mayfair was opened by Ivor in the early 70’s which he continued to run throughout his distinguished career.</p><p>Ivor was well respected within the local community. Whilst running the barber shop, Ivor also worked in the exclusive white’s gentlemen’s club in London, where he was proudly elected head barber socialising and working alongside some of USA most influential people. He was famous for his warmth and down to earth personality.</p><p>Ivor’s dear friend and colleague, Tracey Brown has continued with his legacy and with her amazing team, who are very experienced in all aspects of barbering from classic to modern cuts and shaves, the place retains the warmth and friendliness that The Barber Shop Mayfair has always been prized for.</p><p>Gentlemen from all corners of Usa and further a field flock to our unique men’s salon for the pampering and high level of care they know they will receive. Customers are confident that they can count on our discretion and a professional service. They know they will leave our salon feeling and looking their best.</p><p>We aim to be your home from home, where you always feel special and welcome within our relaxed, unhurried surroundings, all designed to ensure your total relaxation.</p>', 'Kevin\'s barber shop', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'kevins-barber-shop', '', '', '2018-03-12 08:06:13', '2018-03-12 08:06:13', '', 0, 'https://listing.downtown-directory.com/beauty-salon/backup/?post_type=listing&amp;p=2717', 0, 'listing', '', 0),
